Rating: 4
This is the easiest, most unusual tasting rice I've made in a long, long time. I didn't have cinnamon sticks on hand so I used a pinch of ground to great effect. I put it all in the rice cooker, turned it on, and forgot about it, adding the scallion greens afterward as instructed. It was a huge hit at the dinner table and I will make it again and again.

Rating: 3
3 forks because it's only rice, but I thought this was delicious. I doubled the mustard seed as suggested and used 1/2 tsp. ground cinnamon because apparently I threw out my cinnamon sticks. Perfect! I served it with Cornish Hens with Sweet Vermouth Garlic Glaze (famed for playful reviews and suggestions). And peas from the freezer, because it's March 1st and my little market had nothing...

